  "texts": [
    "Now, we will elaborate on the four-step workflow of programmable metasurface agent, as shown in Figure 1f.",
    "First, a user can interact with the programmable metasurface in voice or text format through the LLMs installed in the host computer.",
    "For instance, when the LLM receives the user's request, for instance, \"please illuminate the box_2\", it will decompose the original ambiguous task into a sequence of simple but implementable subtasks, and then generate the implementable Python codes for subtasks.",
    "Second, the LLM will calculate the exact location of \"box_2\" in context of the created 3D visual-semantic map.",
    "Third, the host computer runs the Python code to generate the control coding sequence of metasurface such that the resultant radiation beam can be focused towards box_2."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}